'''
QUESTION 1 â€” Running Simple Containers

ACME cooperation wants to demonstrate micro service for their software to use containers for their applications.
As an initial demonstration, run the container should use nginx.

TASK
- Use the image: podman.io/library/nginx
- The container must be named acme-demo-html
- The container must run in detached mode
- The container's port 80 must be exposed on local port 8001
- The container should map the local file: /home/student/workspace/acme-nginx-html/index.html

'''

SOLUTION
- Navigate to the working directory: cd /home/student/workspace/acme-nginx-html
- Check if the Nginx image already exists locally: podman images
- Pull the required image if it is not available: podman pull podman.io/library/nginx
- Verify the image has been successfully downloaded: podman images
- Create and run the container with the required configurations: 

    podman run -d \
    --name acme-demo-html \
    -p 8001:80 \
    -v /home/student/workspace/acme-nginx-html/index.html:/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html:Z \
    podman.io/library/nginx

- Confirm that the container is running: podman ps | acme-demo.html
- Test and validate the container deployment: 
    - curl http://acme-demo-html:80
    - curl http://localhost:8001
